{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Computes and stores baked lightmaps for fast global illumination."}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot10LightmapGIC","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"LightmapGI"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"LightmapGI","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"class","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"roleHeading":"Class","title":"LightmapGI"},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VisualInstance3D"],"type":"inheritsFrom","title":"Inherits From","kind":"relationships"},{"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GodotObject","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SQ","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SH","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s12IdentifiableP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantRepresentable","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantStorable"]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/lightmapgi"]}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/bias","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/bounceIndirectEnergy","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/bounces","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/cameraAttributes","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/denoiserStrength","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/directional","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/environmentCustomColor","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/environmentCustomEnergy","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/environmentCustomSky","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/environmentMode-swift.property","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/generateProbesSubdiv","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/interior","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/lightData","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/maxTextureSize","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/quality","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/useDenoiser","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/useTextureForBounces"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/godotClassName"],"title":"Type Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/BakeError","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/BakeQuality","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/EnvironmentMode-swift.enum","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/GenerateProbes"],"title":"Enumerations"}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"LightmapGI","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" node is used to compute and store baked lightmaps. Lightmaps are used to provide high-quality indirect lighting with very little light leaking. "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI"},{"text":" can also provide rough reflections using spherical harmonics if ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/directional","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is enabled. Dynamic objects can receive indirect lighting thanks to ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"light probes"}]},{"type":"text","text":", which can be automatically placed by setting "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI\/generateProbesSubdiv","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" to a value other than .disabled. Additional lightmap probes can also be added by creating "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapProbe","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" nodes. The downside is that lightmaps are fully static and cannot be baked in an exported project. Baking a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" node is also slower compared to "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VoxelGI"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Procedural generation:","type":"text"}]},{"text":" Lightmap baking functionality is only available in the editor. This means ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI"},{"text":" is not suited to procedurally generated or user-built levels. For procedurally generated or user-built levels, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VoxelGI","isActive":true},{"text":" or SDFGI instead (see ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Environment\/sdfgiEnabled","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Performance:"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" provides the best possible run-time performance for global illumination. It is suitable for low-end hardware including integrated graphics and mobile devices."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Due to how lightmaps work, most properties only have a visible effect once lightmaps are baked again."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Lightmap baking on "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CSGShape3D","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"s and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PrimitiveMesh","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"es is not supported, as these cannot store UV2 data required for baking."}]}],"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If no custom lightmappers are installed, "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI"},{"text":" can only be baked when using the Vulkan backend (Forward+ or Mobile), not OpenGL.","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note","name":"Note"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/LightmapGI"},"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/s12IdentifiableP":{"type":"unresolvable","title":"Swift.Identifiable","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s12IdentifiableP"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/VariantRepresentable":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VariantRepresentable","kind":"